<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8307179>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Flower diversity in Pauridia. A, P. trifurcillata; B, P. umbraticola; C, P. pusilla; D, P. longituba; E, P. linearis; F, P. gracilipes subsp. speciosa; G, P. curculigoides; H, P. monophylla; I, P.capensis; J, P. canaliculata; K, P. alticola. Photographs by J.C. Paterson-Jones." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8307179/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8307251>
    dc:description "FIGURE 38. Pauridia monophylla. A, whole plant; B, leaf in transverse section; C, stamen in ventral and dorsal views on left and right respectively; D, style and stigma branches; E, ovary in transverse section; F, capsule; G, seed. Scale bar A = 10 mm; B–D = 1.5 mm; E, F = 3 mm; G = 0.5 mm. Drawn by Tracey Nowell from Esterhuysen 37008 (NBG!)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8307251/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8307253>
    dc:description "FIGURE 39. Distribution maps for A, Pauridia monophylla from Western Cape; B, P. curculigoides from Western Cape, South Africa." ;
